Hong Kong is often seen as one of the best global destinations to launch a business. With the Greater Bay Area initiative as a first step, Hong Kong stands to achieve even more recognition as an international center for technological innovation. Hong Kong is also uniquely positioned to create a favorable environment for innovation to blossom in the GBA. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Aaron Liu explains how Hong Kong will contribute to the GBA's development in forming a global innovation and technology hub.